LOCALITY: Brooks Island Regional Preserve (please only use for visits/observations by boat)
TRIP COMMENTS: It was Thanksgiving, a beautiful, calm day with hazy sunshine. Charlie and I took our kayaks to Vincent Park in Marina Bay and put in at the beach. The water could not have been more placid. We kayaked to the spit adjoining the regional shoreline, portaged, and then circled the island. Upon our return, we kayaked along the shoreline of the inner harbor, covering the shoreline near Shimada Friendship Park. The grebes, scaups, and scoters were in the water around the island. The kite, harrier, and a number of other birds were seen on the island or along its shore from the water. When we reached the SF side of the island, the city was covered in fog, and it felt as if we were in Alaska. A harbor seal followed us.

Area 3 of  Ukiah Christmas Bird Count.  Two parties:  Barbara Dolan and John Dane worked north from the south end of the dam to Miti Campground. A second party of Roger Foote, Geoff Heinecken, Greg Cox, and George Chaniot worked south from the inlet to Miti Campground to meet up with the other party.--     06:30 - 15:00  My party covered the area from the inlet south to the barn.  Dreadful heavy rain, high wind from the south.  Everyone got wet.   Mercifully, during the day the temperature was not too cold, Creeka and Lake Mendocino were visably rising.   Had lunch at the barn and decided to head back.  Quit about 13:30.  Drove to Oak Grove parking lot and scoped the Pomo Area with Roger Foote.  It's a good thing we did this because Ollie's team quit at 09:30 and didn't cover it.
